{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1784287049,"nonce":"tgc9Tqax8p0zpiber2XelfEnFrk=","message":"Fixed by PR #109 (squash eac6a5a).\n\nApproach A2 (maintainer-chosen): a dialect-agnostic canonicalization pass,\nsquealy-ir::canonicalize_view_clause_aliases, run on BOTH diff sides in\ncanonicalize_model with a ViewSourceCatalog built from the whole DatabaseModel. It\nexpands a standalone clause alias to its projection expression (the deparser's form)\nand rebinds a nested bare name the source exposes to that source column. New\nSchemaIntrospect seams carry the dialect facts: identifier_case,\ncte_forward_references_visible, recursive_exposes_forward_ctes. The catalog is the\nsoundness guard the reverted e1d0724 inline experiment (cefdd1d) lacked — the\nresolver leaves an ambiguous or unresolved name untouched rather than risk a\nfalse-equal that would skip a needed view replacement.\n\nScope: shipped BOTH shapes (the deparser alias-\u003eexpression rewrite and the\nsource-column collision), not the collision alone, since the broader work was already\nbuilt and live-verified — and shape 2 alone is a no-op on SQLite (below).\n\nKEY EMPIRICAL CORRECTION to this bug's premise: the collision shape does NOT churn on\nSQLite and never did. SQLite stores verbatim CREATE VIEW text, so introspection parses\nthe clause back into the same bare form the desired model authored and both sides\nalready compare equal. Proven by disabling the pass: the SQLite test still passes while\nthe PostgreSQL live test churns exactly the CreateView described here. The pass is\nload-bearing for PostgreSQL/MySQL only (their deparsers rewrite the clause); SQLite\nneeded only the dialect wiring. The SQLite replan-empty test added here records that\nnegative result.\n\nAlso fixed a real stack overflow found while reviewing: the clause walker used\nmap_scope_exprs_mut, which applies its closure pre-order then descends into the\nalready-replaced node, so a self-referential alias (x + 1 AS x — reachable from\nhand-authored SQL or KDL, this bug's exposure surface) re-expanded forever. A\nBareColumn now resolves as a leaf whose replacement is not re-descended.\n\nVerified: fmt; clippy -D warnings; 958 tests passed / 0 failed; compile_fail; live\npublish -\u003e introspect -\u003e replan-empty on PostgreSQL (4/4) and MySQL (11/11) plus\nsquealy-model (7/7); local codex review clean. CI test + MSRV green.","files":null}]}